### Finding 9 of 12 — High

**File**: `crates/mementor-lib/src/pipeline/ingest.rs:183-432`

**Issue**: `run_ingest` is ~250 lines with `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]`. It handles 5 concerns: (1) session loading, (2) transcript parsing, (3) raw entry/PR link insertion, (4) turn processing (chunk+embed+store), (5) session state update. Extracting concerns (3) and (4) into helpers would remove the lint suppression.

**Before**:
```rust
#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]
pub fn run_ingest(
    conn: &mut Connection,
    embedder: &mut Embedder,
    session_id: &str,
    transcript_path: &Path,
    project_dir: &str,
    project_root: &str,
) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    // ... 250 lines handling all 5 concerns inline
}
```

**After**:
```rust
pub fn run_ingest(
    conn: &mut Connection,
    embedder: &mut Embedder,
    session_id: &str,
    transcript_path: &Path,
    project_dir: &str,
    project_root: &str,
) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    // ... session loading + parsing (concerns 1-2)

    insert_raw_data(conn, session_id, &raw_entries, &pr_links)?;  // concern 3

    // ... turn grouping

    process_turns(conn, embedder, session_id, &turns, ...)?;  // concern 4

    // ... session state update (concern 5)
}

fn insert_raw_data(...) -> anyhow::Result<()> { ... }
fn process_turns(...) -> anyhow::Result<(usize, Option<usize>)> { ... }
```

Splits the monolithic function into smaller helpers, removing `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` and making each piece independently readable.

